EWE data for the NW Atlantic

ewe_nwatlantic_base.Rd

Ecopath with Ecosim data for the Northwest Atlantic ocean, where each data object is from a different run. E.g., base is from the base model run and env is from the run using environmental variables.

Usage

ewe_nwatlantic_base

ewe_nwatlantic_env

Format

EWE NW Atlantic

A tibble with 35640 rows and the following 10 columns:

file_name

The path to the file name, note that the path could be a relative path. This column is helpful for understanding which EWE model and which run the data came from.

type

The type refers to what data type this row is, e.g., landings, catch, biomass, weight, and mortality.

year

A four-digit integer specifying the year.

month

A one- or two-digit integer specifying the month.

function_group

A string specifying the functional group that this row pertains to.

value

A real number containing the value of interest.

fleet

An integer specifying which fleet the data pertains to.

An object of class tbl_df (inherits from tbl, data.frame) with 35640 rows and 10 columns.

Source

https://www.github.com/nmfs-ost/

References

Chagaris, D., Drew, K., Schueller, A., Cieri, M., Brito, J., and Buchheister, A. 2020. Ecological reference points for Atlantic menhaden established using an ecosystem model of intermediate complexity. Frontiers in Marine Science, 7:606417. 10.3389/fmars.2020.606417.
